<p>There were no significant differences in plasma protein binding observed between the two groups. The effects of Zoloft in patients with moderate and severe hepatic impairment have not been studied [See Dosage and Administration 2.</p>
<p>Renal Impairment Sertraline is extensively metabolized and excretion of unchanged drug in urine is a minor route of elimination. Thus sertraline multiple dose pharmacokinetics appear to be unaffected by renal impairment [See Use in Specific Populations 8.</p>
